ble. here are my thoughts. If you dont agree or have changes please add your own pros cons.<br>
<br>
Mob is reserveable: Opinion on which<br>
Pro<br>
Con<br>
<br>
Fire Giants: Cahnge to FFA<br>
Pro's: It is a training ground for smaller guilds to practice raid skills.<br>
<br>
Con's: <br>
With all the expansion's, there are plenty of places for potential raid leaders to hone their skills.<br>
The giants are doable by a single group or less.<br>
The giants are frequently not reserved on any given day.<br>
8 hour respawns mean that they can be done 2-3 times a day by interested parties.<br>
The loot on them is no longer significant compared to new items, The crown seems to be the most sought after item.<br>
<br>
<br>
Naggy, and Vox(resons are same for both): Remain as is.<br>
Pro's: <br>
Limit of 52 sets a practical limit on who can do these dragons.<br>
Lesser raid experience of these player's will be aided by the additional time to prepare.<br>
Their is no hardship in scheduling a date for these mobs.<br>
<br>
Con's: not having scheduled raids could mean that these mobs go down even less than they do currently.  <br>
<br>
Venril Sathir: Chane to FFa<br>
Pro's:<br>
He is a rare mob, those seeking to kill him for whatever reason will eventually get a turn.<br>
<br>
Con's:<br>
--He is exactly like drusilla in HS, but she is not reservable. Just not the same demand for her.<br>
--Doable by a single group or very small raid.<br>
--I've heard rumors about guild reserving epic items for those that are no where near able to complete their epic's. Ie lvl 45 wizards getting staff. I think this will just slow down the competition for these items.<br>
--His items are nice but not necessarily the best available at this time. (like drusilla and the nos). Not to say his loot isnt still rather nice.<br>
--Recent Changes will make him more accessible.(hopefully)<br>
<br>
Trakanon: Remain as is<br>
Pro's:<br>
--The list is not long, Therefore those seeking a turn are assured of one in a reasonable time.(may change eventually).<br>
--Needed element of VP key, which some are more able to utilize than others.<br>
--At this time I feel the current system works well to assure equal opportunity.<br>
--As more people level, I believe this mob will become more popular for a time, but interest will wane as vp keys are aquired, and new expansions are introduced.<br>
<br>
Cons: <br>
--Loot is average but nice. <br>
--None of the other dragons of like level are reservable.<br>
--<br>
<br>
Plane of Fear/Hate: Remain As is.<br>
Pro's: <br>
--Dates are readily available to anyone willing to put forth the effort to claim one.<br>
--Can only be clear once per day average, 3 times every 2 days, but hours are very odd.<br>
--It would be a shame to loose the raid feeling with individual camps for sepearate spawns occuring. <br>
--First real raid experience for high level players, still a nice training area for guild teamwork.<br>
--loot mobs are primarily needed by 50ish people who benefit from advance planning available with a scheduled system.<br>
--Higher level groups are unable to get to the higher mobs without reserving a date, and clearing out a significant portion of loot mobs which they no longer need. I think this would be exacerbated by a ffa system. This could be worked around by partnership raids.<br>
--Note: I dont believe Extending the Calendar to 3 weeks will help the situation. It will fill up 3 weeks, and you will still be forced to camp the board 3 weeks out for a date.<br>
<br>
Con's:<br>
--Higher level groups are unable to get to the epic and higher mobs without reserving a date. Could be worked around with partnership raiding.<br>
<br>
<br>
Plane of Air: Remain as is<br>
Pro's: <br>
--This plane is not in great demand to my knowledge. It is set up for 24 people. it requires a high level group to complete the plane.<br>
<br>
