              -Chris Titus Wisdom<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unicophorus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nicophorus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://homepages.go.com/~aela_eq/Shield.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Less Talk, More Fight </span><br>  Posts: 850<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/5/01 7:56:17 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://homepages.go.com/~aela_eq/Shield.gif border=0></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Reasons Why. Pros cons</span><hr size=1> Actually, your argument isn't accurate.<br>
<br>
The 'cons' you list for Fire Giants aren't Cons (as in negatives), they are alternative ideas that have no positive or negative value.<br>
<br>
The Con Azzi added is the only actual 'negative' being lumped into the FG issue... and its also false.<br>
<br>
Fire Giants have yet to make Ragefire stay spawned any length of time... so, Fire Giants are NOT causing fewer Cleric epics to hit the server.<br>
<br>
The FG reservations have impacted WHO got that epic on occaision (once this past weekend), but it did NOT cause a Ragefire spawn to either (A) go to waste, nor did it cause (B) Ragefire to sit idle.<br>
<br>
Were either of those points true, then yes Rage WOULD be a con for FG's... but they aren't true, so that con is not true.<br>
<br>
Additionally, the following pro of the FG system as it stands:<br>
<br>
Provides Nagafen raiders with some degree of certainty that Fire Giants wont be repopping in the middle of a Nagafen raid.  We KNOW the relative time of death and respawn because of the scheduled raids.  We KNOW that Fire Giants aren't raided on Naggy days without direct coordination with the Nagafen raid leader (who has precedence).  I imagine Magus Rokyl repopping in the middle of a Nagafen fight would be... bad.  I imagine that Fire Giants repopping as people logged in from buff circle could be... at the very least... a setback to a raid that already leans towards too long.<br>
<br>
For some reason that one gets overlooked... its too convenient to focus on FG reservations as the bottleneck (it isn't) and just making it FCFS will help your Cleric get their epic sooner (it WONT).<br>
<br>
1) Verants stated policy is NOT FFA/FCFS... the ACTUAL stated policy is a preference that players work out a system by themselves and maintain it... FCFS will only be enforced by Verant when the players have shown too little maturity to arrive at their own system... somehow that gets distorted by FFA advocates...<br>
<br>
2) Because very few players play eight hour sessions (see one of your CON's), the ability to reserve a spawn of this duration helps to assure that WHOMEVER wants to take a shot at it has some reason to believe that the creatures will be there when they go there.<br>
<br>
There ARE valid reasons for FCFS/FFA/and even reservations... however, nothing used as a 'reason' for FCFS in this thread has actually been one of them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm50.showMessage?topicID=7.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm50.showMessage?topicID=31.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm50.threadControl?topicID=10.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm50.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=10.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm50.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=10.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="brellserilisfrm48">Town Crier (Rules & Announcements)<option value="brellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion">The Commons (General EQ Discussion)<option value="brellserilisfrm56">Salutations & Congratulations <option value="brellserilisfrm50">Calendar Discussion<option value="brellserilisfrm33">Dreams & Diversions (Off Topic)<option value="brellserilisfrm59">It Takes a Village... Idiot<option value="brellserilisfrm36">Improve this Board<option value="brellserilisfrm55">Fellowship of Guilds (Guildchat)<option value="brellserilisbrellslairadminonly">Brell's Lair (